# ThreadSanitizer suppressions
#
# GCC 11 (Ubuntu 22.04) libtsan FALSE POSITIVES in EventBus concurrent push/pop.
#
# Root cause: libtsan-11 mismodels std::condition_variable::wait_for
# (pthread_cond_timedwait), losing the happens-before edge provided by mutex_,
# then reports a spurious "double lock of a mutex" at EventBus::push and a
# cascade of races on the mutex-protected std::queue/deque.
#
# Proven FALSE (not a real bug — do NOT change EventBus):
#   1. A real double-lock of a non-recursive std::mutex would DEADLOCK, but the
#      test passes in ~4.6s.
#   2. TSan lists BOTH racing accesses as holding the same mutex (M33); a real
#      race needs at least one access without the common lock.
#   3. The join-first test (no concurrent push+pop) is TSan-clean; only the
#      condvar-in-pop concurrent case trips it.
#
# Re-verify (and ideally drop these) on GCC >= 13 or clang, where the condvar
# modeling is fixed.

mutex:bbb::EventBus::push
deadlock:bbb::EventBus::push
race:bbb::EventBus::push
race:bbb::EventBus::pop
